sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / CI
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Webhook as spark-operator-webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as spark-operator-controller
    participant SparkSubmit as spark-submit<br/>(local exec)
    participant Driver as Spark Driver Pod
    participant Executor as Spark Executor Pods<br/>7078/TCP, 7079/TCP

    Note over User,Executor: Flow 1: SparkApplication Submission

    User->>K8sAPI: POST SparkApplication CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kubeconfig
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-sparkoperator-...<br/>443→9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated SparkApplication<br/>(defaults applied)
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-sparkoperator-...<br/>443→9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation result
    K8sAPI-->>User: SparkApplication created

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch SparkApplication CRs<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: SparkApplication event (New)

    Controller->>SparkSubmit: Local exec spark-submit
    SparkSubmit->>K8sAPI: Create Driver Pod<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate--v1-pod<br/>443→9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Pod (volumes, env injected)

    Note over Controller: State: Submitted → Running

    Driver->>K8sAPI: Create Executor Pods<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>Auth: SA token (spark-operator-spark)
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate--v1-pod<br/>443→9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Executor Pods

    Driver->>Executor: Spark RPC communication<br/>7078/TCP, 7079/TCP plaintext

    Note over Controller: State: Running → Completed/Failed

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update SparkApplication status<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS

    Note over User,Executor: Flow 2: ScheduledSparkApplication

    User->>K8sAPI: POST ScheduledSparkApplication CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Note over Controller: Cron trigger fires
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create SparkApplication CR<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Note over Controller: Follows Flow 1 steps

    Note over User,Executor: Flow 3: Spark Connect Server

    User->>K8sAPI: POST SparkConnect CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Connect Server Pod + Service<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS

    participant Client as Client Application
    Client->>Driver: gRPC connection<br/>15002/TCP plaintext
    Driver->>Executor: Spark RPC<br/>7078/TCP, 7079/TCP plaintext
